        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(imessage): stage remote media before plugin dispatch",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Stage remote inbound media during dispatch before plugin hook and plugin-bound inbound-claim metadata is built.\n- Mark successfully staged remote media as already staged so the later agent reply path does not restage the same attachment.\n- Add regressions for SCP remote-cache rewriting, plugin-bound Codex claim metadata, and Codex `localImage` turn input.\n\n## Linked context\n\nCloses #91744.\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: remote iMessage attachments that start as raw macOS Messages paths are staged before plugin-bound Codex inbound claims are constructed, so the Codex-visible media metadata uses the local remote-cache path instead of `/Users/.../Library/Messages/Attachments/...`.\n- Real environment tested: fresh worktree `/Users/andy/openclaw-91744-imessage-codex-staged-path` based on live `upstream/main` `9a1f2022b127f27312eeb7f57e42d477bddf2c19`, using repo test runners and local runtime modules.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n  - `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply.message-hooks.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply.stage-sandbox-media.scp-remote-path.test.ts extensions/codex/src/conversation-turn-input.test.ts extensions/imessage/src/monitor.media-policy.test.ts extensions/imessage/src/channel-inbound-roots.contract.test.ts -- --reporter=dot`\n  - `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.ts src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply.stage-sandbox-media.scp-remote-path.test.ts extensions/codex/src/conversation-turn-input.test.ts`\n  - `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.ts src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply.stage-sandbox-media.scp-remote-path.test.ts extensions/codex/src/conversation-turn-input.test.ts`\n  - `git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD`\n  - `OPENCLAW_CHECK_CHANGED_REMOTE_CHILD=1 OPENCLAW_CHANGED_LANES_RAW_SYNC=1 CI=1 PNPM_CONFIG_VERIFY_DEPS_BEFORE_RUN=false pnpm check:changed`\n- Evidence after fix: focused acceptance tests passed 3 Vitest shards: auto-reply 3 files / 207 tests, extension-codex 1 file / 8 tests, extension-imessage 2 files / 6 tests. `check:changed` completed successfully across core, coreTests, and extensionTests lanes.\n- Observed result after fix: the SCP staging regression replaces a raw `/Users/demo/Library/Messages/Attachments/.../photo.jpg` input with a staged path under `CONFIG_DIR/media/remote-cache/<session-slug>/photo.jpg` in both `ctx` and `sessionCtx`, with real staged bytes present. The dispatch regression verifies staging runs before the plugin-bound inbound claim and that the claim metadata contains only the staged cache path. The Codex regression verifies that final turn input emits `localImage` with the staged remote-cache path, not the original Messages path.\n- What was not tested: a live remote Mac/iMessage conversation, because this environment does not have live remote Mac/iMessage credentials.\n- Proof limitations or environment constraints: local SCP proof mocks only the external `scp` child process, but exercises the real `stageSandboxMedia()` copy/rewrite path, dispatch metadata path, and Codex turn-input conversion.\n- Before evidence: #91744 and the ClawSweeper issue review showed plugin-bound Codex inbound claims were built before remote staging, allowing raw macOS attachment paths to reach Codex metadata.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\nCommands run:\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply.message-hooks.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply.stage-sandbox-media.scp-remote-path.test.ts extensions/codex/src/conversation-turn-input.test.ts extensions/imessage/src/monitor.media-policy.test.ts extensions/imessage/src/channel-inbound-roots.contract.test.ts -- --reporter=dot`\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.ts src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply.stage-sandbox-media.scp-remote-path.test.ts extensions/codex/src/conversation-turn-input.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.ts src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply.stage-sandbox-media.scp-remote-path.test.ts extensions/codex/src/conversation-turn-input.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD`\n- `OPENCLAW_CHECK_CHANGED_REMOTE_CHILD=1 OPENCLAW_CHANGED_LANES_RAW_SYNC=1 CI=1 PNPM_CONFIG_VERIFY_DEPS_BEFORE_RUN=false pnpm check:changed`\n\nRegression coverage added:\n\n- SCP remote staging success rewrites raw remote iMessage paths to the local remote-cache path.\n- Dispatch stages remote iMessage media before plugin-bound Codex inbound claim metadata is built.\n- Codex turn input uses the staged remote-cache path as `localImage`.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\n- Did user-visible behavior change? `Yes`\n- Did config, environment, or migration behavior change? `No`\n- Did security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? `Yes`\n- Highest-risk area: remote media staging now runs earlier in dispatch for remote inbound media, before plugin hooks and plugin-bound claims.\n- Mitigation: the new dispatch staging is gated on `MediaRemoteHost`, a session key, inbound media, and `!MediaStaged`; successful staging marks `MediaStaged` to preserve the single-stage contract for later agent processing. Existing path policy and size checks remain in `stageSandboxMedia()`.\n\n## Current review state\n\n- Next action: CI and ClawSweeper review.\n- Waiting on: normal PR checks and durable ClawSweeper verdict.\n- Bot/reviewer comments addressed: implements the issue review direction to stage before plugin-bound Codex claim metadata is derived.\n\nAI-assisted: yes.\n",
